<TITLE> Nikita, family remanded for 3 days </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 9 (bdnews24.com)  Suspected drug peddler Jannatul Ferdous Nikita, her parents and her brother were Friday remanded in RAB custody for three days for questioning. RAB-3 second-in-command Maj Mobinur Rashid said the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka granted the law enforcers three days to quiz the suspects. Investigation officer RAB sub-inspector Selim Badshah had appealed for a five-day remand. Ramna police chief ABM Doulat Akbar said the case investigation had been transferred to RAB. According to police's preliminary investigation report, Nikita's father Abdun Noor, mother Saleha Khatun and brother Moyeen Uddin were aware of her illegal business. Police and RAB arrested Nikita and Hotel Purbani International managing director Mahbubur Rahman Joynal Sunday. Mohammadpur Police Station sub-inspector Siddique Khan said three of the four cases against Joynal filed with them had been transferred to RAB for investigation. bdnews24
